kages. Gain a deep understanding of the project's architecture, intended features (Agent Discovery & Coordination, VS Code Integration, Workflow Automation, API Services), the Model Context Protocol (MCP), and the project's overall goals. Development Environment Setup & Dependency Resolution (Firebase Studio & Local Docker): Analyze Setup: Examine all package.json files across the monorepo, yarn.lock (or equivalent), and the compose.yaml file. Resolve Dependencies: Identify and fix all dependency installation and configuration errors within the Firebase Studio environment and for local Docker-based development. This includes: Ensuring Corepack is correctly enabled and used for Yarn 3.x as mentioned in the Dockerfiles. Resolving any version conflicts, deprecated packages, or missing dependencies. Making sure all setup scripts (e.g., ./consolidated-build.sh, ./scripts/mcp-setup.sh, ./scripts/launch-mcp-wizard.sh) are fully functional and error-free. Docker Environment: Ensure the Docker Compose setup (COMPOSE_BAKE=true docker-compose -f compose.yaml up -d --build) builds successfully without errors. Verify all services (frontend expected at http://localhost:3000, backend API at http://localhost:3001) start, run correctly, and are accessible. Confirm that all service paths referenced in compose.yaml are correct and that there are no references to missing or obsolete services (e.g., message-broker, chrome-extension, frontend/simplified have been noted as removed). Environment Variables: Identify all required .env files (e.g., apps/backend/.env, apps/frontend/.env). Provide a clear template or list of all required environment variables for each service. Since you cannot access actual secret values, guide me on how to define and populate them correctly. Firebase Studio: The primary goal here is to make the development environment within Firebase Studio fully operational and stable for this project. Phase 2: Codebase Health and Feature Completion TypeScript Error Eradicati